:wave: Hello, team! Recently a faced a problem with embed videos. So far as videos were hosted on vidyard and played using directly their API.
I was using it to control video in response to user actions.
Few days ago something change in way HubSpot embed this videos, now  they are hidden behind iframe and UUID(vidyard ID) are also hidden, so I cant find videos on page by VidyardV4 Library and control it.
I can't find also any docs from HS about this changes and how to control embed video players now.

Do you know what is going on, and how to solve this problem?
Below example of code which was working perfectly, and now can't find players.
```{{ require_js("<https://play.vidyard.com/embed/v4.js>", { position: 'head', async:
true }) }}```
```{% require_js %} 
&lt;script&gt;
$(function() {
  window.onVidyardAPI = (vidyardEmbed) =&gt; {
    vidyardEmbed.api.addReadyListener((_, player) =&gt; {

    let playerUUID = $(".{{ name }} .vidyard-player-container").attr("uuid")

      $(".{{ name }} .video-cover, .{{ name }} .video-icon ").click(
        function() {
          $(".{{ name }} .video-cover").hide();
          $(".{{ name }} .video-icon").hide();
          $(".{{ name }} .vidyard-player-wrapper").addClass("show");
		  let players = VidyardV4.api.getPlayersByUUID(playerUUID);
          players[0].play();
        }
      ); 
}, )
}
}); 
&lt;/script&gt;
{% end_require_js %} ```
